Nat(ural) Ambio(phonis) Surround
================================================================================

natambio is a real-time JACK audio application that combines two processing
stages on live audio streams:

  1. Panambio  - PCA-based spatial decomposition of a stereo signal into
                 main + ambience components (front mode) or surround signal
                 (rear mode), driven by a 2x2 covariance eigenvalue solver
                 running in dedicated real-time worker threads.

  2. Convolution - per-channel partitioned FFT convolution via Fons
                   Adriaensen's zita-convolver library, configurable as
                   arbitrary routing graphs (chained convolvers, bypass via
                   the "delta" coefficient, per-output gain and delay).

Both stages are driven by a single XML configuration file. The two stages can
run in one JACK client (Panambio -> Convolution chained internally) or split
across two JACK clients (natambio + smoothfir blocks in the same file).


Features
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 - XML configuration (libxml2), with `~` home-directory expansion for paths.
 - Up to 64 convolution channels (the zita-convolver limit).
 - Many-to-many routing: any input port can feed multiple convolvers; any
   convolver can drive multiple output ports; convolver outputs can feed
   other convolver inputs.
 - "delta" bypass coefficient for pass-through paths with gain and delay only.
 - Panambio outputs available as JACK ports OR as virtual buffers consumed
   directly by downstream convolvers (no JACK round-trip).
 - Sample-accurate per-channel output delay and linear gain.
 - Impulse responses loaded from any libsndfile-supported audio format
   (mono channel selectable, sample rate must match JACK).
 - Derived coefficients: a <coeff> may be built at load time from the
   convolution of one or more other coeffs (via <convol_coeff>) instead of
   from an audio file, so composite filters (e.g. RACE * EQ) can be assembled
   directly from the configuration.


Dependencies
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 - JACK            (jack/jack.h)
 - zita-convolver  (Fons Adriaensen, https://kokkinizita.linuxaudio.org)
 - libsndfile      (impulse response file loading)
 - libxml2         (configuration parsing)
 - fftw3f          (single-precision FFT, pulled in by zita-convolver)
 - pthreads, librt


Build and install
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
With the autotools build system:

    ./autogen.sh        # only needed when building from a git checkout
    ./configure
    make
    sudo make install

A simple fallback Makefile is also provided under src/:

    cd src && make

The installed binary is `natambio` (default prefix /usr/local).


Usage
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    natambio [-quiet] <configuration-file.xml>

Use Ctrl+C (SIGINT) to stop.

Several example XML configurations are provided under tests/.
A full description of the XML schema is in README.CONFIG, and an extended
developer reference is in src/README.md.


